name: Alcohol Dehydrogenase – ADH1A sticky spheres
description:
Alcohol dehydrogenase is a dimeric enzyme that catalyzes the oxidation of alcohol to acetaldehyde in the body. Specifically for humans, this is the rate-limiting step for ethanol metabolism, converting ethanol to acetaldehyde. ADH1A also makes important modifications to fatty acids, retinol, and steroids.
